// Istio Ambient Mode install steps

Reference: https://github.com/bugbiteme/ossm-3-demo

1. Do normal ./install_operators.sh

2. Do all steps in "Set up Tempo and OpenTelemetryCollector"

3. For "Set up OSSM3" Use the OSSM3Ambient folder 

  3a.. oc new-project istio-system
  
  3b. oc apply -f istioambientcr.yaml
  
  3c. oc create namespace istio-cni
  
  3d. oc label namespace istio-cni istio-discovery=enabled
      oc label namespace istio-system istio-discovery=enabled
      oc apply -f istioambientCni.yaml
      
  3e. oc create namespace ztunnel
      oc apply -f ztunnel.yaml
      
  3f. oc create namespace bookinfo
      oc apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/istio/istio/master/samples/bookinfo/platform/kube/bookinfo.yaml -n bookinfo
      oc label namespace bookinfo istio.io/dataplane-mode=ambient
      
  3g. Validate with: istioctl ztunnel-config workloads $ZTUNNEL_POD -n ztunnel | grep bookinfo
  
  3h. oc apply -f waypointgateway.yaml
      oc label namespace bookinfo istio.io/use-waypoint=bookinfo-waypoint
      
  3i. oc apply -f ./resources/TempoOtel/istioTelemetry.yaml  -n istio-system
      oc label namespace opentelemetrycollector istio-injection=enabled
      
4. Do all steps in "Set up OCP user monitoring workflow"

5. Do all steps in "Set up Kiali"

6. Do the first two commands in "Set up BookInfo"

7. Go back to OSSM3Ambient folder

  7a. oc apply -f bookinfogateway.yaml
      oc apply -f routebookinfo.yaml
      
  7b. oc get route bookinfo-edge -n bookinfo -o jsonpath='{.spec.host}
  
  7c. Edit the HTTPRoutebookinfo.yaml resource in OSSM3Ambient with the route in the HTTPRoute.spec.hostnames field with the full route path 
      oc apply -f HTTPRoutebookinfo.yaml 

8. Test the route with curl

CLUSTER_URL=$(oc get route bookinfo-edge -n bookinfo -o jsonpath='{.spec.host}')

curl -I http://$CLUSTER_URL/productpage




